  "executive_brief_md": "## HAVCR2 \u2014 hepatitis A virus cellular receptor 2\n\n**White Space score 48.07/100 \u00b7 rank 2/13 \u00b7 HIGH confidence.** Top-tier white space \u2014 validated, tractable, and comparatively uncrowded within the IO cohort.\n\nHAVCR2 is a cell junction target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: Hepatitis A virus cellular receptor 2 inhibitor. Competitive footprint: 3 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: subcutaneous panniculitis-like T-cell lymphoma, neoplasm, myelodysplastic syndrome, non-small cell lung carcinoma.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.7521, Tractability 0.9, Saturation 0.2898 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
